data.enText: a wide road, where traffic can travel fast for long distances and that drivers must pay a toll to use

tr: an expressway on which tolls are collected
(from 16th to 19th centuries) gates set across a road to prevent passage until a toll had been paid

value.def: A turnpike is a road, especially an expressway, which people have to pay to drive on.
value.tran: 收费公路;(尤指)收费高速公路
